Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Although... it might be difficult to persuade the Jarl to allow you to use his palace as a dragon trap... | I'm sure you'll manage, though. If you can defeat the World-Eater, surely sweet-talking the Jarl of Whiterun isn't beyond you.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinD1: Go on...

Cell.Text: Did you find the Elder Scroll? What happened when you took it back to the Throat of the World?

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinBlockingTopic: I have good news.

Cell.Text: He must have returned to Sovngarde to feed on the souls of the dead. | If you don't find him soon, he'll return, stronger than ever!

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinTopic: I defeated Alduin, but he escaped. I need to find him.

Cell.Text: Yes, yes. We must think. He must have some means of travelling to and from Sovngarde. But no tale tells where that might be.
Don't worry. I have a plan. I'm going to trap a dragon in Dragonsreach.
[S] The Jarl's palace in Whiterun? Ah, yes... the old story about King Olaf's pet dragon. Ingenious!

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinA1: I know. That's why I need to find him.

Cell.Text: Very true! Hmm. I wonder... do you know the Jarl's palace in Whiterun?

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinA2: His dragon allies must know where this portal is...

Cell.Text: Yes, exactly! Most people don't know that it was originally built to hold a captive dragon - hence its name.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinB1: You mean Dragonsreach?

Cell.Text: Oh, this was thousands of years ago, before the Akaviri crusaders cleansed Skyrim of dragons. | Skyrim's mountains were still infested with dragons. One of the early Nord kings caught a dragon and kept it in Dragonsreach.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinC1: I thought there weren't any dragons until Alduin came back.

Cell.Text: [S] You could trap him there, exactly.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinC2: So if I could lure a dragon into Dragonsreach...

Cell.Text: Well, you see, the palace - Dragonsreach - was originally built to hold a captive dragon. Hence its name.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernFindAlduinB2: What's the Jarl's palace have to do with this?

Cell.Text: What's happened? Did you find a way to learn the Dragonrend Shout?

Node.Caption: MQ301DelphineIntroTopic: I defeated Alduin.

Cell.Text: G|Esbern should be able to help. He's spent his whole life poring over every old book he could find about dragons and that prophecy. | He's been digging around the records the Blades left here, too. But we can talk about that later.

Node.Caption: MQ301DelphineIntroA1: I used Dragonrend on Alduin, but he escaped.

Cell.Text: Shout for Odahviing from the Dragonsreach courtyard. After that, it's up to you.
I need a way to lure a dragon to Dragonsreach. Any ideas?
Interesting problem. Hmm. Yes. I've been poring over the records here in Sky Haven Temple.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonTopic: How can we lure a dragon to Dragonsreach?

Cell.Text: I anticipated the problem. While you were arranging this meeting, I was busy in the library of Sky Haven Temple.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonBlockingTopic: How can we lure a dragon to Dragonsreach?

Cell.Text: Ah, don't you see? The names of dragons are always three Words of Power -- Shouts. | By calling the dragon with the Voice, he will hear you wherever he might be.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonA1: How does that help us?

Cell.Text: He's not compelled to, but dragons are prideful by nature and loath to refuse a challenge. | Your Voice in particular is likely to intrigue this dragon, after your victory over Alduin. | I think it very likely that he will be unable to resist investigating your call.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonB1: Why would he come when called?

Cell.Text: Ah, indeed. I'm no master of the Voice like these worthy gentlemen, but it is written here in this scroll.
Ah, indeed. I'm no master of the Voice like the Greybeards, but it is written here in this scroll.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonC1: So what's this dragon's name?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> An unguessed trove of lost lore... but the important thing is that the Blades recorded many of the names of dragons they slew. | Cross-referencing this with Delphine's map of dragon burial sites, and I believe I've identified one of the dragons that Alduin has raised up.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonIntro1

Cell.Text: Odahviing will come to your challenge. Broziik. Krilot. He will not be able to resist your call, from the Hill of the Dovah itself... he will come.
I need a way to lure a dragon to Dragonsreach. Any ideas?

Hmm, yes. I have been pondering on exactly that question. Lingrah morah. | I have tasted the voices of Alduin's allies on the wind. Pogaan nahlaas, vokrii wah jun. | There is one who I remember well. Odahviing. He is the one to tell us where Alduin has gone.

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxCallDragonTopic: How can we lure a dragon to Dragonsreach?

Cell.Text: Ah, I forget how little you know of the dov. Our names are always made up of three Rotmulaag - Words of Power. | You see - Paar-thur-nax - a thu'um - a Shout, yes?

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxCallDragonA1: So we know his name. How does that help me get him to Dragonsreach?

Cell.Text: He is not compelled to come, but the dov are prideful by nature. Few could resist such a challenge. Especially from you, Dovahkiin. | But Odahviing, he is... headstrong? Boziik. Rash. Even among the dov, he was known for this. | He will not resist the challenge of your Voice, Dovahkiin. He will come.

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxCallDragonB1: Why would he come when called?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Now - hear his name. Odahviing. Taste it on the wind. Od-ah-viing. Know it in your su'um. Od-ah-viing!

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxCallDragonC1: So what's this dragon's name?

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Od - Ah - Viing. "Winged Snow Hunter", as I read it.

Node.Caption: MQ301EsbernCallDragonD1

Cell.Text: There's one more thing. We know about Paarthurnax.
I'm afraid there's a further problem. A serious one. I've discovered who the Greybeards' leader really is.
I'm afraid there's a problem. A serious one. I've discovered who the Greybeards' leader really is.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroTopic: What about Paarthurnax?

Cell.Text: Paarthurnax. The dragon, that the Greybeards have been protecting for all these years.
You've discovered... what?
He's a dragon. Not just any dragon, but the right hand of Alduin, responsible for many atrocities during the ancient Dragon War.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroA1: You know... what?

Cell.Text: [S] He needs to die. He deserves to die. And it falls to you to kill him. | Until he's dead... well, I'm sorry, but we would dishonor our oaths as Blades if we continued to help you.

[S] The Blades have been hunting him for centuries, but he was protected by the Greybeards and then the Emperors. | Justice demands that he die for his crimes. Until he is dead, I'm afraid my oath as a Blade prevents me from offering you aid and comfort.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroB1

Cell.Text: That's fine. We needed his help. Now we don't, and it's long past time for him to pay for his crimes. | And he's not just any dragon. He was the right hand of Alduin. | He committed atrocities so infamous they are still remembered, thousands of years later.

All well and good. But did you know that he was Alduin's chief lieutenant in ancient times? Responsible for terrible atrocities? | It's true that his crimes are long in the past, but justice does not count the passage of years.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroA2: Turns out he's a dragon. But he helped me.
